   <text source="#civic">
      <body>
         <div type="record_set">
            <div type="record" source="#tallow_chandlers">
               <head>
                  <title>Tallow Chandlers’ Wardens’ Account Book, 1549-1585</title>
                  <bibl source="#london-metropolitan-archives">LMA:
                     CLC/L/TC/D/001/MS06152/001</bibl>
                  <supplied>6 August 1557-6 August 1559</supplied></head>
               <gap/>
               <pb type="folio" n="68v"/>
               <label>(Wardens accounts payments for election day feast)</label>
               <note type="marginal" place="margin_left">Mynstrell<ex>es</ex> &amp; players</note>
               <table>
                  <row>
                     <cell role="label">Paid to the mynstrell<ex>es</ex></cell>
                     <cell role="data">viij s.</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell role="label">paid more w<ex>i</ex>th the consent of the maisters of oure
                        companie to the said mynstrell<ex>es </ex>in rewarde for mondaie</cell>
                     <cell role="data">iij s. iiij d.</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell role="label">paid to the Boyes of the hospital for the playe on
                        mondaie</cell>
                     <cell role="data">v s.</cell>
                  </row>
               </table>
               <gap/>
               <pb type="folio" n="69v"/>
               <label>(Inventory of goods in the hall dated 28 September 1559)</label>
               <label><hi rend="center">In the parlor</hi></label>
               <gap/>
               <ab>ij olde bancars lyned</ab>
               <gap/>
               <list>
                  <item>A Targett w<ex>i</ex>th the Armys of the haul</item>
                  <item>A squytchen w<ex>i</ex>th iij tirtle doves</item>
               </list>
               <gap/>
               <desc><hi rend="center">In the haull</hi></desc>
               <gap/>
               <list>
                  <item>A gilt Beame w<ex>i</ex>th v latyn candilstick<ex>es </ex>w<ex>i</ex>th the
                     ymage of o<ex>u</ex>r lady and A Tirtle dove w<ex>i</ex>th iiij latyn cheynes
                     longe or short,</item>
                  <item>ij Clothes, the one of the ymage of the Assumpcion of o<ex>u</ex>r ladie and
                     the other of oure ladie and Seynt Elizabeth,</item>
                  <item>A Gylded lyon of woodd</item>
                  <item>xiiij Targett<ex>es </ex>great and small,</item>
               </list>
               <gap/>
               <pb type="folio" n="70r"/>
               <label><hi rend="center">In the court house</hi></label>
               <gap/>
               <list>
                  <item>A chest wherein are iiij disgysed cott<ex>es </ex>of canves w<ex>i</ex>th
                     iij hood<ex>es </ex>for correction</item>
                  <item>iiij Streymers of reee silke</item>
                  <item>iij flagg<ex>es </ex>of Silk good and bade</item>
                  <item>ij Streymers grene, the one of the picture of Seynt Peter and the other of
                     the Armys of London of the gifte of M<ex>aste</ex>r John Mery</item>
                  <item>iiij small flagg<ex>es </ex>
                  </item>
                  <item>vij small pensell<ex>es </ex>
                  </item>
               </list>
               <gap/>
               <label><hi rend="center">In the yarde</hi></label>
               <gap/>
               <list>
                  <item>v pec<ex>es </ex>of tymber for the companie to stonde vppon at
                     eu<ex>er</ex>y tryomphe,</item>
                  <item>vj banner Staves good and badde,</item>
               </list>
               <gap/>
               <pb type="folio" n="72r"/>
               <label>(Orders in the time of the 1557-59 wardens. 11 July 1559)</label>
               <gap/>

               <table>
                  <row>
                     <cell role="label">This daie it was agreed that whereas of olde tyme there
                        hathe byne no more but v s. Allowed to the mynstrell<hi rend="italic">es
                        </hi>of the Election dynner daie/ the m<hi rend="italic">aste</hi>r Wardens
                        &amp; Assistauntis thynke yt good &amp; be so determined that the
                           mynstrell<hi rend="italic">es </hi>shall haue for the election dynner
                        daie nowe next com<hi rend="italic">m</hi>ynge</cell>
                     <cell role="data">-x s.</cell>
                  </row>
               </table>
            </div>
         </div>
      </body>
